content.description: The big tall boulder. Great problem on decent sandstone. Starts low with small holds and nice feet, work your way up into a thin crux to the victory jug up top.
content.location: Furthest boulder from the road, just uphill from the largest and first boulder you run into. Walk the small trail created by the river, up and around the rock to the left and down into a little nook.

content.description: Start with hands on the shoulder height sloppy edge, move right and up on more sloppers. There is a sit start that probably  goes around V6. It involves a left hand dyno from a sit on smeared feet and a shallow right crimp to the starting holds of the stand start.
content.protection: You'll definitely want a pad on the boulder to your back.
content.location: There is a nice little concentration of boulders directly uphill from the munson boulders that are right off the road. However, it is close enough that it should just be included in the area. There were absolutely no signs that any of these boulders had been climbed or attempted or that people had even been up in the area.
